    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but i've seen some people arguing that the UN is basically just a relic of the post-WWII era and isn't even relevant anymore given how much power the P5 members actually hold. do most historians see that kind of \"obsolete\" argument as a valid critique, or is it just seen as an unrealistic view of how global diplomacy works?",
